  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Ann Arbor, Michigan, businessman and local historian, graduate of the Ann Arbor High School and the University of Michigan. Thayer was drafted into the U.S. Army in 1994 and served on a tank crew in the 3rd Armored Division, Company D, 32nd Regiment. Thayer fought and was wounded in the Battle of the Bulge, and was awarded a Purple Heart.</subfield>
    <subfield code="b">After World War II Thayer returned to Ann Arbor where he operated an insurance company. After Thayer retired, he became an author and historian of the American circus. He died in 2009.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Thayer's letters home dating from August 1944 to June 1946, from Fort Knox, Kentucky, Washington, D.C., and locations in Belgium, Italy, France, Austria, and Germany. Letters describe daily life and activities, training, military hospitals, and local towns and customs.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Research papers, dated 1977-1978, include notes prepared with Patricia O'Toole concerning St. Patrick's Catholic Church, Northfield Township, Washtenaw County; paper concerning early Michigan circus history; and paper entitled, "Stephen Mills - Early Washtenaw County Builder."; also photographs.</subfield>
  </datafield>
